com.inqwell.any.client

Class AnyComponentEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractComposite
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractMap
        • com.inqwell.any.PropertyAccessMap
          • com.inqwell.any.client.AnyComponentEditor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, InqEditor, Composite, EventListener, Map, Serializable, CellEditor, TableCellEditor, TreeCellEditor

    public class AnyComponentEditor
extends PropertyAccessMap
implements TableCellEditor, TreeCellEditor, InqEditor, EventListener
    An all purpose editor, handling table cells and tree cells

    Acts as a container for an underlying editor which does all the real work.

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.9 $
    Author:
    $Author: sanderst $

                               int col,
                               Any colName,
                               TreeLevel level,
                               BooleanI isLeaf,
                               BooleanI expanded)
        Description copied from interface: InqEditor
        Determine whether editing should be started in the specified cell.
        Specified by:
        canStartEditing in interface InqEditor
        Parameters:
        parentComponent - the parent tree, table or list
        contextNode - the current context
        rowRoot - root node from which cell value is referenced
        value - value of cell
        row - row number
        col - column in model coordinates (table and tree table only)
        colName - column name, if available (table and tree table only)
        isLeaf - if a tree editor, whether the node is a leaf. Null if not a tree
        expanded - if a tree editor, whether the node is expanded. Null if not a tree
        Returns:
        true if editing can be started, false if it cannot
